# About Me
## Who I Am
My Name is Ruby Ballard, I am a senior at Alta High School. AI interests me because its becoming very relevant in todays world. It also has a lot of cool features that I would like to learn more about. The fact that you can feed information into AI and it can come back at you with a response is so cool to me.

Specific parts of AI I want to work on is being able to feel information into an AI program. I don't want to just make prompts for AI, I want to make prompts for AI that will help other engineers. This matters to me because if I can feed information into AI it can give the the answers to problems i want to solve, and the more I train it on a specific thing the more my knowledge will grow on it.

My perspective on this is unique because instead of my interests on making an AI for a specific problem I want to solve instead of just feeding a little bit of everything into it. I want to make prompts for generalized AI.

Key Focus Areas:
- Machine Learning Algorithms
- Prompt Engineering
- Clear communication, creativity
- feeding information into AI
## What Drives Me
Problems I want solved with AI is the problem with a lot of big companies use different designing programs, I want an AI that can help teach people things like Fusion, solid-works, and a bunch of other design programs.
## About This Portfolio
This portfolio will contain a lot of carefully constructed prompts for AI that will help people with learning more about designing and building machines in industries, it will also help people with a bunch of other interests. There will also be examples of how they can be used in the real world.

My Approach:
To create prompts for AI in this, I will test and re test prompts that I write until it can provide accurate results that are useful to what the person is asking for.
